author: Matt Wixon
title: In McKinney North's Justin Madubuike, Texas A&M's Kevin Sumlin gets star DE, occasional sprinter
text:
Texas A&M got another big commitment today when McKinney North defensive end Justin Madubuike announced that he has committed to the Aggies:
Happy to say that I have committed to The Texas A&M Aggies! #Gig 'em #ItsAboutUs
â” Justin Madubuike (@JMadubuike15) September 18, 2015
Here's some background on Madubuike, who was the SportsDayHS preseason pick for Defensive Player of the Year:Madubuike was an all-district selection as a sophomore, and as a junior he took a step toward becoming McKinney North's best lineman ever. He was the 10-5A Defensive MVP after making 75 tackles and piling up 16 1/2 sacks and causing four fumbles.
In the spring, Madubuike worked on his speed while competing with the track team as one of the biggest sprinters you'll ever see. Every time Madubuike lined up for the 100 meters at a meet, someone would ask, "Hey, are you a football player?"
Madubuike is considered by many as one of the nation's top 100 recruits in the Class of 2016.
